coverage. It seems like normal use would require the provider to be installed or specified, which makes sense. I think the generated test needs to call Conscrypt.newProvider() or include it somehow. But then, I wonder if that’s considered “beyond normal generated test scaffold.” Typically, the scaffold test probably starts off empty, and any usage code would come from the agent, right?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying provider setups**\\n\\nI'm looking at a concrete provider but wondering about the surrounding environment. Existing tests point to functionality, but does no_action imply no setup? It might still need agent guidance. JSON includes a relevant field, which is puzzling. The goal seems to be determining a deterministic setup without generic usage guidance. It’s interesting that the existing agent can research but is asking about typical library usage to finalize the setup. Plus, there could be an external dependency for generating certs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting JVM tests**\\n\\nI’m considering that if we run tests on the JVM without using add-opens, there’s a chance they could fail. However, it looks like `javaTest` might actually use add-opens. I think it would be a good idea to look at the open-source Conscrypt README to check its setup for Java 9 modules. Let’s see if I can search for that and gather more information!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pqkBfrgwnyCtFH85JnF0abqL|fc_028604bc4e8ea44f016a42de10cb20819493218cd95903e5fe", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nfor name in ['README.md','BUILDING.md','CAPABILITIES.md']:\n data=urllib.request.urlopen(f'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/google/conscrypt/master/{name}', timeout=20).read().decode('utf-8','replace')\n print('\\n---',name,'---')\n for term in ['add-opens','native.workdir','provider','Security.insertProviderAt','enable-native-access']:\n  i=data.lower().find(term.lower())\n  if i!=-1: print(term, data[max(0,i-300):i+500])\nPY", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1996, "output": 1711, "cacheRead": 47616, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51323, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782767089871, "responseId": "resp_028604bc4e8ea44f016a42ddf3047c8194ad92f36a94ca2b8a"}}
