.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Use Conscrypt explicitly in tests rather than assuming it is the default JCA/JSSE provider: call Conscrypt.checkAvailability(), create Provider provider = Conscrypt.newProvider(), and pass that provider to JCA/JSSE factories such as SSLContext.getInstance(\\\"TLS\\\", provider), or temporarily install it with Security.insertProviderAt in test setup and restore providers afterward. Preserve the existing Java/native test JVM arguments that open java.base/java.lang, java.base/java.net, and java.base/sun.nio.ch when exercising socket and platform internals. No org.conscrypt.native.workdir setting is needed unless the test environment's default temp directory is noexec or unavailable.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported native-image runtime failure appears tied to Conscrypt JNI/native-image/JDK internals rather than to a missing external service or dependency.\",\n    \"Conscrypt extracts and loads a bundled native library at runtime; unusual temp-directory permissions can require org.conscrypt.native.workdir, but there is no evidence that the standard Ubuntu CI environment needs it.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_028604bc4e8ea44f016a42de1fce088194b236d51338706b0a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1690, "output": 817, "cacheRead": 51200, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53707, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782767124999, "responseId": "resp_028604bc4e8ea44f016a42de15cce48194a32ca5dee589e56e"}}
